    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "grpc/grpc have a whole repo level mechanism to generate test coverage. Reports can be found deeply hidden inside Fusion (our CI platform) under the build [`prod:grpc/core/master/linux/grpc_coverage`](https://fusion.corp.google.com/projectanalysis/current/KOKORO/prod%3Agrpc%2Fcore%2Fmaster%2Flinux%2Fgrpc_coverage?search_pattern=grpc_coverage&include_inactive_projects=false). An example report can be downloaded [here](https://storage.cloud.google.com/grpc-testing-kokoro-prod/test_result_public/prod/grpc/core/master/linux/grpc_coverage/307/20190125-112421/github/grpc/reports/coverage_report.zip?_ga=2.158711858.-964109803.1538005757).\r\n\r\nIn that case, IMO there is no point to program a less useful tooling... We should reconsider how to promote the test coverage result, and how to act on it."
